es": [], "notes": "All required repository visibility indicators exist in the dataset."}, "detection_logic": "1. Initialize counters: total_repos = 0 and public_repos = 0. 2. Iterate through each record in the dataset. 3. For each record where _asset_type equals ''github_repo'': increment total_repos by 1. 4. Read visibility and is_private values as strings. 5. If visibility equals ''PUBLIC'' OR is_private equals ''False'', mark this repository as publicly exposed and increment public_repos by 1. 6. Record a detail entry with status ''fail'' and message ''Repository <name> is publicly exposed (visibility=PUBLIC or is_private=False)''. 7. Otherwise record a detail entry with status ''pass'' and message ''Repository <name> is not publicly exposed''. 8. After evaluating all repositories: if public_repos > 0 return overall result ''fail''. 9. If public_repos == 0 return overall result ''pass''.", "configurable_args": [], "test_scenarios": [{"scenario_name": "all_private_repositories", "result_expectation": "pass", "dataset_record_ref": "record_1"}, {"scenario_name": "obvious_public_repo", "result_expectation": "fail", "dataset_record_ref": "record_4"}, {"scenario_name": "another_public_repo", "result_expectation": "fail", "dataset_record_ref": "record_5"}, {"scenario_name": "private_archived_repo", "result_expectation": "pass", "dataset_record_ref": "record_6"}, {"scenario_name": "empty_dataset", "result_expectation": "pass"}], "ssf_mapping": {"standard": "custom", "event_type": "github-repository-publicly-exposed", "event_uri": "", "custom_event_uri": "https://kcontrol/signals/github/repository/public_visibility", "signal_severity": "high", "subject_type": "repository"}, "expected_output_format": {"result": "pass | fail | warning", "summary": "N/M repositories are publicly exposed", "details": [{"check": "repository_public_visibility", "status": "pass|fail|warning", "message": "detail"}]}, "spec_locked": false, "approved_at": null}', '2026-03-26T01:24:52.903066', '2026